<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,493,1050,1110]" box="[151,410,1085,1110]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,160,1085,1110]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">(</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[160,256,1085,1109]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Plate 1E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[268,401,1085,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-72@14.[177,1408,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–39. Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov. (32) pygofer, lateral view; (33) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (34) right style, lateral view; (35) right style, dorsal view; (36) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (37) aedeagus, ventral view; (38) connective, dorsal view; (39) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 33–39</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1157,1901]" box="[151,630,1157,1181]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,1157,1181]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 7.80 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1157,1901]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,462,1193,1217]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Moderate sized, robust species. General color concolorous black, except for yellow costa on forewings and yellow crown (
<figureCitation box="[593,692,1229,1253]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Plate 1E</figureCitation>
); face yellow and black, clypeus and genae yellow, clypellus and lorae black. Head broad, nearly as wide as pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, about as wide as width of eyes, slightly produced anteriorly, disk flat, lateral margins convergent basally; eyes large, nearly globular; pronotum slightly longer than crown, surface bullated; mesonotum large, about twice as long as pronotum; forewings long, broad, 3 anteapical cells present, outer one closed; clypeus long, broad, median longitudinal carina very faint; clypellus short, about as 1/3 long as clypeus, lateral margins broadly expanded in distal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1157,1901]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,374,1445,1470]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view elongate, distal half broad with large tuft of setae on caudoventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[202,285,1481,1505]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-72@14.[177,1408,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–39. Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov. (32) pygofer, lateral view; (33) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (34) right style, lateral view; (35) right style, dorsal view; (36) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (37) aedeagus, ventral view; (38) connective, dorsal view; (39) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate very long, slender, setaceous in distal 1/5 (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1112,1481,1505]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-72@14.[177,1408,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–39. Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov. (32) pygofer, lateral view; (33) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (34) right style, lateral view; (35) right style, dorsal view; (36) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (37) aedeagus, ventral view; (38) connective, dorsal view; (39) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
); style long, about as long as aedeagus, robust, distal ¼ curved, attenuated in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[848,979,1517,1541]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-72@14.[177,1408,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–39. Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov. (32) pygofer, lateral view; (33) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (34) right style, lateral view; (35) right style, dorsal view; (36) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (37) aedeagus, ventral view; (38) connective, dorsal view; (39) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs.35, 36</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, narrow, tubular, with 3 moderately long, medial spines, row of very short spines distad and adjacent to medial spines (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1364,1553,1577]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-72@14.[177,1408,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–39. Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov. (32) pygofer, lateral view; (33) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (34) right style, lateral view; (35) right style, dorsal view; (36) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (37) aedeagus, ventral view; (38) connective, dorsal view; (39) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 37. 38</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Y-shaped, stem very short, medial rib present, membranous on each side of middle; dorsal connective long, narrow (
<figureCitation box="[358,442,1625,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1849,1872]" captionTargetBox="[201,1399,218,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-72@14.[177,1408,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–39. Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov. (32) pygofer, lateral view; (33) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (34) right style, lateral view; (35) right style, dorsal view; (36) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (37) aedeagus, ventral view; (38) connective, dorsal view; (39) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
